\begin_layout Standard
Let 
\begin_inset Formula $S$
\end_inset

 denotes the sample space of a given experiment and 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathcal{A}$
\end_inset

 a collection of events.
 We say that 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathcal{A}$
\end_inset

 is an 
\emph on
algebra
\emph default
 over 
\begin_inset Formula $S$
\end_inset

 if the following two conditions are fulfilled:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
\begin_inset Formula $S$
\end_inset

 must be an element of 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathcal{A}$
\end_inset

, i.e.
 
\begin_inset Formula $S\in\mathcal{A}$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
if 
\begin_inset Formula $E_{1}\in\mathcal{A}$
\end_inset

, 
\begin_inset Formula $E_{2}\in\mathcal{A}$
\end_inset

, the sets 
\begin_inset Formula $E_{1}\cup E_{2}$
\end_inset

, 
\begin_inset Formula $E_{1}\cap E_{2}$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $E_{1}\setminus E_{2}$
\end_inset

 must also belong to 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathcal{A}$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Interpretation: an algebra 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathcal{A}$
\end_inset

 over 
\begin_inset Formula $S$
\end_inset

 is a family of subsets of 
\begin_inset Formula $S$
\end_inset

 which is closed with respect to the three binary operators 
\begin_inset Formula $\cup,\cap\mbox{ and }\setminus$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Example
a) The collection given by 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathcal{A}=\{S,\emptyset\}$
\end_inset

 is an algebra (the so called 
\emph on
trivial
\emph default
 algebra over 
\begin_inset Formula $S$
\end_inset

).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Example
b) The collection 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathcal{A}=\{E,\bar{E},S,\emptyset\}$
\end_inset

 is the algebra generated by 
\begin_inset Formula $E\subset S$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Example
c) The power set of 
\begin_inset Formula $S$
\end_inset

, i.e.
 the collection consisting of all the subsets of 
\begin_inset Formula $S$
\end_inset

 (including the empty set 
\begin_inset Formula $\emptyset$
\end_inset

).
\end_layout

